Project: Lego Simulator
A browser-based app that takes a text description or image as input, and generates a 3D voxelized Lego representation of it on a 100x100 baseplate (100 units vertical as well).
How it works

User provides a description or uploads an image
If an image, Gemini recognizes what it is
The input gets decomposed into primitives
The app builds the Lego representation from those primitives
AI validates the result and tweaks if needed
The result is shown to the user for feedback
User can provide feedback to refine
Final output is displayed in a 3D voxel space

What this is

An AI-powered generator — the user describes or shows something, and the app figures out how to represent it in voxelized Lego form
The building is done by the AI, not by the user placing bricks manually

What this is NOT

Not a manual brick-by-brick building tool
Not a physics simulation
Not a multiplayer or social tool


Rules for working in this codebase
Before making any changes, scan the full codebase and understand:

How state flows — where state lives, what manages it, and how components read/write to it. Don't introduce a new state pattern.
Existing logic loops — trace the full pipeline from input (description/image) through decomposition, building, validation, feedback, and rendering. Extend these flows, don't create parallel ones.
What's intentionally missing — if something seems like an obvious feature but isn't implemented, assume it was deferred on purpose. Don't add it as a side effect of your change.
Naming and file conventions — match the existing patterns for file names, function names, folder structure, and component organization.
Performance assumptions — don't introduce optimizations or abstractions that aren't already in use unless I specifically ask for them.

When you're ready to make a change:

Describe which existing files/functions you'll touch and why
Flag if your change would affect any other flow
Keep the change as minimal as possible
If you're unsure about a design decision, ask before implementing
